    .md-modal#fulkerson-modal
      .content
        .image
          h3.name Ford-Fulkerson Visual
        .description
          p This application provides a visual representation of the
            | &nbsp#[a(target="_blank", href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ford%E2%80%93Fulkerson_algorithm") Ford-Fulkerson]
            | algorithm - a popular algorithm for
            | determining the maximum flow of a directed flow network. The user has the ability to construct a custom
            | flow network and view how the algorithm chooses paths for augmenting flow. A user may use this application
            | to learn how the Ford-Fulkerson algorithm works, or study its edge cases by comparing various methods for
            | choosing augmenting paths (breadth first search, depth first search, fattest path).
          p This Ford-Fulkerson visual was built in March 2016 as a final, independent project for a 4th year algorithms
            | course at The University of Western Ontario. The application was completed in approximately one week, and a
            | final grade of 90% was received.
          p The project was built using #[a(target="_blank", href="https://d3js.org/") D3], a JavaScript library for
            | building visualization components based on data. As I already had some experience using D3 for a thesis
            | project, and was aware that it had the capabilities to create the application I had in mind based on other
            | applications I discovered, D3 seemed like the best choice. Other technologies that I used include Node.js,
            | ES6, #[a(target="_blank", href="https://mochajs.org/") Mocha] and
            | #[a(target="_blank", href="http://chaijs.com/") Chai].
          p This project was an excellent learning experience. Not only did it vastly increase my knowledge of D3, I also
            | took the opportunity to learn more about ES6 (the new JavaScript standard) and employed test-driven development
            | where I could using Mocha and Chai.
        .actions
          a(target='_blank' href='#')
            button Try It!
          a(target='_blank' href='https://github.com/jerridan/ford-fulkerson-visualization')
            button View Source
    .md-modal#guidebook-modal
      .content
        .image
          h3.name Guidebook
        .description
          p Guidebook is a tool that employers can use to create simple, custom training material and exercises for their
            | employees. Digital pages can be filled with videos, images, short quizzes and text boxes, which can then
            | be accessed by employees who are given access.
          p I worked on this application with a team of developers and designers during my time at
            | #[a(target="_blank", href="http://icomproductions.ca/") &nbspICOM Productions Inc.],
            | an e-learning solutions company in Calgary, AB. The project was a huge success, with multiple employers
            | purchasing it before development had finished, and continues to be offered by ICOM.
          p The front-end of Guidebook was built with React, while the backend was built with PHP. Other tools like
            | &nbspReflux, Immutable, Node.js, webpack and LESS were also used.
          p This project was my first experience using React, which quickly became my favorite JavaScript tool for
            | building user interfaces. The majority of my work was spent on the front-end, where a good deal of my focus
            | was on creating the interactive quiz modules and styling the application according to Google's Material Design.
        .actions
          a(target="_blank" href='projects/guidebook_screenshot.jpg')
            button Screenshot
