    .md-modal#hooli-modal
      .content
        .image
          h3.name Hooli Drive
        .description
          p Hooli Drive is a client-server file transfer system. It works via 3 main programs - the
            | client, a database server, and a file upload server. The client scans a specified directory for files and
            | sends the file names and checksums to a database server over a TCP connection. The database server responds
            | with a list of new or modified files, which the client will then send to the upload server over a reliable
            | UDP connection.
          p This application was built over the course of 3 separate assignments for a 3rd year computer networking
            | &nbspcourse at The University of Western Ontario, and achieved a final grade of 102.5%.
          p Hooli Drive was built with C on an Ubuntu 14.04 Vagrant machine, and uses Redis for the database.
          p While coding in C can be tedious, I enjoyed the learning experience and came to a greater appreciation for
            | &nbspthe language. I value the knowledge I gained in using TCP and UDP, as well as the
            | #[a(target="_blank", href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stop-and-wait_ARQ") Stop-and-Wait] UDP protocol.
        .actions
          a(target='_blank' href='https://github.com/jerridan/hooli_drive')
            button View Source
